data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":203,"item_id":"msg_0856f50ac9a8287300693a0793d16c8197945debb73e4eaefe","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has a detailed Whistleblower Policy designed to promote a safe and transparent workplace. The policy encourages employees, contractors, and third parties to report any unethical or illegal activities. Key aspects include:\n\n1. **Definition:** A whistleblower is someone who reports activities that are illegal, unethical, or not in accordance with company policy.\n\n2. **Reporting Procedures:** Reports can be made by contacting the Human Resources Department, emailing the Compliance Officer at compliance@contoso.com, or calling the Compliance Hotline at 1-800-555-1212. Details such as time, date, involved parties, and evidence are encouraged.\n\n3. **Retaliation Prohibited:** Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited, with disciplinary actions for any violations.\n\n4. **Confidentiality:** The whistleblower’s identity will be kept confidential as permitted by law.\n\n5. **Investigation:** All reports will be investigated thoroughly to ensure proper action is taken.","logprobs":[]}

